29/01/2010
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki and Greek Alternate Foreign Minister Dimitris Droutsas agreed Thursday (January 28th) to ask UN mediator Matthew Nimetz to intensify talks on their countries' long-standing name dispute.
Milososki and Droutsas met in London on the sidelines of an international conference on Afghanistan.
Nimetz is expected to visit Macedonia and Greece in about a month.
Milososki said Athens has reservations about Macedonia's initiative to raise existing liaison offices in Skopje and Athens to the level of embassy.
He added that the Greek Finance Ministry is looking into Skopje's initiative to sign an agreement on double taxation avoidance.
(MIA, Makfax, A1, Sitel - 28/01/10)
